Let's extract the necessary numbers and perform the calculations step by step.

1. Current Ratio  
   Use the Total Current Assets and Total Current Liabilities (from the balance sheet at end date).  
   • Total Current Assets = 14,619,619.72  
   • Total Current Liabilities = 7,605,149.91  
   Calculation: 14,619,619.72 ÷ 7,605,149.91 ≈ 1.92  

2. Gross Profit Margin  
   From the income statement, use Gross Profit and Total Revenue.  
   • Gross Profit = 279,378.77  
   • Total Revenue = 775,598.77  
   Calculation: (279,378.77 ÷ 775,598.77) × 100 ≈ 36.00%  

3. Debt to Asset Ratio  
   In this simplified case, total liabilities are the current liabilities because no separate non-current liabilities are given.  
   • Total Liabilities = 7,605,149.91  
   • Total Assets = 23,717,525.01  
   Calculation: 7,605,149.91 ÷ 23,717,525.01 ≈ 0.32  

4. Net Profit Margin  
   From the income statement, use Net Profit and Total Revenue.  
   • Net Profit = 112,375.10  
   • Total Revenue = 775,598.77  
   Calculation: (112,375.10 ÷ 775,598.77) × 100 ≈ 14.49%  

5. Cash to Current Debt Ratio  
   The cash available is calculated by summing Cash on Hand and Bank Deposits.  
   • Cash on Hand = 2,067,352.98  
   • Bank Deposits = 3,752,082.80  
   Total Cash = 2,067,352.98 + 3,752,082.80 = 5,819,435.78  
   • Total Current Liabilities = 7,605,149.91  
   Calculation: 5,819,435.78 ÷ 7,605,149.91 ≈ 0.77  

6. Free Cash Flow (FCF)  
   FCF is calculated as Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities minus Capital Expenditures (in this case, Purchase of Fixed Assets).  
   • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -967,147.02  
   • Capital Expenditures = 1,213,417.20  
   Calculation: -967,147.02 - 1,213,417.20 = -2,180,564.22  

7. Return on Assets (ROA)  
   Using Net Profit and Total Assets from the balance sheet.  
   • Net Profit = 112,375.10  
   • Total Assets = 23,717,525.01  
   Calculation: (112,375.10 ÷ 23,717,525.01) × 100 ≈ 0.47%  

Thus, the final results are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Current Ratio": "1.92",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "36.00%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.32",
    "Net Profit Margin": "14.49%",
    "Cash to Current Debt Ratio": "0.77",
    "Free Cash Flow (FCF)": "-2180564.22",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "0.47%"
  }
}
